rComments: Overall great class. Pr. Trentin really knows a lot about what she is teaching and she presents it in a very interesting way. Honestly was scared at first because of the reviews I saw, so I am happy I didn't listen to them because I really enjoyed the class. The midterm and exam are exactly as she describes them.

Knowledgable Prof. She tells you exactly what to study. Plenty of opportunities to raise your grade between midterm and exam, even extra credit opportunities. The assignment was a bit tough, but Dr Trentin gives you excellent feedback. She's extremely caring and wants everyone to succeed. Lots of participation marks so attending class is important.
Dr. Trentin is super awesome. She's a renowned scholar and a great teacher. She makes everything interesting, but she is also very demanding. I will take more courses from her for sure.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Dr. Trentin is an excellent professor. Very smart and articulate. She knows her stuff, and she knows how to frame it in a way that is provocative and interesting. Expect to work, but also to be amazed.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Dr. Trentin was a great professor! She's a clear, expressive speaker and her interest in what she teaches is apparent. She loves to ask questions to raise discussion. As for CLA101 however, it is very demanding. There are weekly readings, weekly quizzes, 4 papers and a very long exam. The entire Iliad, parts of Aeneid and History of Rome are read.

rComments: I don't care how much you love Percy Jackson; unless you are planning on majoring in Classics, don't take this course. The prof is a bit cocky, as others have said. Expect weekly quizzes & discussions, and boring lectures. The characterization essay was a little difficult, and we had a 3 hour written exam (no M/C). Beware. NOT a bird (easy) course!

rComments: Firstly, this class is good if you are majoring in Classics or you are passisonate about it. I took it to get my credit for humanties and honestly I learned more from reading the book than I did from her.  She isn't a bad person but her teaching style is not suited for me personally.

rComments: Do not take this course unless you plan on majoring in Classics or are extremely passionate about it. The course is excessively hard. Weekly quizzes, long readings, and Trentin herself feels she is better than her students. Took it as an elective and totally screwed up my GPA. Kinda hot though.

WORST prof I have ever had. Most definitely did some favours to get the job. She gives long and boring lectures, gives no effort towards ensuring students understand the content and she is very cocky and arrogant. I am in 3rd year and she was awful. She twitches her eyes when she thinks she's right, tests are brutally long. Assumes u memorize iliad

she is so boring  she thinks she knows everything and assumes that you already know it. her ta's are great, but she is awful. unless you are extremely passionate about classics don't take this class its brutal. don't take this as a bird course it will ruin your average. almost  couldn't get into second year because of this. she's hot tho hahaha
More work than I have had in any other class. Tough grader. LONG assignments. Avoid.

She is not a humble teacher, she tries to prove how she knows everything in a know it all fashion. The tests are very long, if you hate essay questions be aware that those are the only types of questions. Her multiple choice are very hard and require you know the readings cover to cover. She isn't there for her students.

Her teaching styles are cruel. She force feeds you information in a "full of herself" manner. She is a tough marker and it's impossible to fight her on any grade she gives you. She is very unapproachable and will avoid you if you see her outside of class time. If you want a teacher who is there for you and your education, avoid her.

Enjoyable and interesting class if you like the material. Not a bird course. GO TO OFFICE HOURS AND GET TO KNOW HER, SHE'LL TELL YOU STUFF!  She knows how to keep both conversations and lectures interesting, has a great sense of humor.  Her midterm was fair if you did the readings. Exam was long but apparently not as bad as past years.
this teacher is a horrible person she thinks she's so much better than all the students and she cares about no one
